@EnexabitWebSocketProject.API_HostAddress = http://localhost:5253

### Register a new user
POST {{EnexabitWebSocketProject.API_HostAddress}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "password": "pass123",
  "displayName": "Alice"
}

### Login
POST {{EnexabitWebSocketProject.API_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "password": "pass123"
}

### Refresh token (cookie sent automatically)
POST {{EnexabitWebSocketProject.API_HostAddress}}/api/auth/refresh

### Logout (replace <token> with actual JWT)
POST {{EnexabitWebSocketProject.API_HostAddress}}/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer <token>

### List all channels (replace <token>)
GET {{EnexabitWebSocketProject.API_HostAddress}}/api/channels
Authorization: Bearer <token>

### Get messages for channel 1 (replace <token>)
GET {{EnexabitWebSocketProject.API_HostAddress}}/api/channels/1/messages
Authorization: Bearer <token>

### Send a message to channel 1 (replace <token>)
POST {{EnexabitWebSocketProject.API_HostAddress}}/api/channels/1/messages
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <token>

{
  "text": "Hello from REST!"
}

### SignalR hub (for reference — connect via JavaScript client)
# WebSocket: ws://localhost:5253/channelHub?access_token=<token>